129
00:14:29,640 --> 00:14:33,570
 Wu Hyeon...

130
00:14:35,980 --> 00:14:38,260
 What is it?

131
00:14:38,260 --> 00:14:43,650
 I want to go to the restroom...

132
00:14:47,890 --> 00:14:50,590
 What? Do you want me to come with you?

133
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:52,720
 Yes.

134
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,090
 Go by yourself!

135
00:14:54,090 --> 00:14:55,340
 No, you are coming with me.

136
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:58,730
 Hey! Stop pushing me!

137
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:30,900
 On the winter solstice, it's the day with the longest night,

138
00:15:30,900 --> 00:15:35,150
 so many ghosts go around that night.

139
00:15:37,350 --> 00:15:39,520
 It's me, Wu Hyeon.

140
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:43,010
 Seriously, Baek Wu Hyeon!

141
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:45,950
 I'm sorry. I didn't know you'd be this surprised.

142
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:47,650
 You freaked me out!

143
00:15:47,650 --> 00:15:49,600
 I'm sorry.

144
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:53,400
 Hey, careful!

145
00:15:54,270 --> 00:15:55,410
 Lee Yu Ri.

146
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:57,100
 Yes?

147
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:01,890
 Why are you not giving me a nickname?

148
00:16:02,580 --> 00:16:04,210
 What?

149
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:10,580
 Why don't you give me a nickname like you did to Yong Jun?

150
00:16:11,550 --> 00:16:15,890
 Do you think coming up with a nickname is that easy?

151
00:16:15,890 --> 00:16:20,000
 Just name me anything like you did to Yong Jun.

152
00:16:22,690 --> 00:16:26,210
 It's cold out. Let's go home.

153
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:35,790
 Guys, there's something in there!

154
00:16:35,790 --> 00:16:39,380
 It was a time full of nothing useful.

155
00:16:39,380 --> 00:16:42,900
 And that's why it was a more beautiful time.

156
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:49,840
Wu Hyeon must be doing great, right?

157
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,410
What is this?

158
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:15,680
Can I take a look?

159
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:17,310
What?

160
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:33,250

161
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,350
It's awesome.

162
00:17:37,270 --> 00:17:39,880
Do you want it?

163
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:42,610
Can I take it?

164
00:17:43,440 --> 00:17:46,030
Yes, you can take it.

165
00:17:46,780 --> 00:17:48,560
Thank you.

166
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:56,130
Your grandmother must be looking at auroras every day in the heavens, right?

167
00:18:01,020 --> 00:18:05,440

168
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:21,860

169
00:19:30,830 --> 00:19:32,690
 What's this?

170
00:19:32,690 --> 00:19:34,400
 Open it.

171
00:19:39,040 --> 00:19:42,040
 I won't be around on Christmas this year.

172
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:46,050
 So?

173
00:19:46,050 --> 00:19:50,130
 So I'm giving you your present early. The twenty-fourth is your birthday.

174
00:19:51,770 --> 00:19:53,630
 You didn't have to give me an early present.

175
00:19:53,630 --> 00:19:57,660
 You can miss a birthday once in a while.

176
00:19:57,660 --> 00:20:00,950
 Don't catch a cold again because of your cold feet.

177
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:18,930
 It's very warm.

178
00:20:24,860 --> 00:20:26,920
 Don't look at me.

179
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:35,070
 Guys, look at this! It's so cute!

180
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:37,410
 What is it?

181
00:20:37,410 --> 00:20:39,660
 Merry Christmas!

182
00:20:39,660 --> 00:20:43,510
 Those hats are for the children's story-telling time, so don't destroy them.

183
00:20:43,510 --> 00:20:45,450
 - Yes. 
 - Why are you wearing it like this?

184
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:47,620
 - Why? 
 - Give me one, too.

185
00:20:47,620 --> 00:20:49,120
 There's nothing for you.

186
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:51,080
 Give me one, too!

187
00:20:51,080 --> 00:20:53,230
 Oh, really.

188
00:20:53,230 --> 00:20:55,020
 - Hey! 
 - Oh, no!

189
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:59,900
 - Grandma, say something to him! He always hits me! 
 - Are you snitching that?

190
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:02,020
 - Why are you guys always fighting? 
 - This is how you wear this hat!

191
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:03,830
 - No, this is right. 
 - This is right.

192
00:21:03,830 --> 00:21:07,000
 - I told you this is right. Let me fix it for you. 
 - Grandma, I wore it better, right?

193
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:10,460
 - Come here! 
 - Guys, stop it.

194
00:21:21,760 --> 00:21:24,220

195
00:21:24,220 --> 00:21:27,480
You have to eat dinner together...

196
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:52,570

197
00:22:07,860 --> 00:22:09,900
- Are you not going to work? 
 - I'm working right now.

198
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,380
What kind of work is that?

199
00:22:11,380 --> 00:22:14,410
Reading fortune for the store is part of my job.

200
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:15,950
Gosh!

201
00:22:15,950 --> 00:22:19,140
Stop fighting each other! It's too noisy for me to sleep.

202
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:22,290
Seriously! Waiting tables is your job, Dad.

203
00:22:22,290 --> 00:22:25,380
Do I have to wait tables while cooking as well?

204
00:22:25,380 --> 00:22:27,650
I worked a lot during the afternoon.

205
00:22:27,650 --> 00:22:30,000
So are you not going to wrap things up?

206
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,160
You must do a better job as a dad.

207
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:33,640
You don't have a sense of responsibility.

208
00:22:33,640 --> 00:22:35,090
I just fell asleep for a second.

209
00:22:35,090 --> 00:22:38,700
Do you have to bring up my sense of responsibility because I dozed off for a second?

210
00:22:38,700 --> 00:22:40,920
Seriously, for f**k's sake...

211
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:43,500
What? Did you just curse at me?

212
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:48,080
I can't do this anymore.

213
00:22:50,120 --> 00:22:53,570
Do whatever you want. We will share your paycheck, so it's good for us.

214
00:22:53,570 --> 00:22:55,680
It's good for us.

215
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:58,590
It's super annoying!

216
00:23:01,230 --> 00:23:04,170
I'm sorry to bother you in the middle of the conversation.

217
00:23:04,170 --> 00:23:06,810
I saw the ad that you are hiring a part-timer.

218
00:23:06,810 --> 00:23:08,770
Oh goodness, it's already dinner time.

219
00:23:08,770 --> 00:23:10,620
Really?

220
00:23:10,620 --> 00:23:14,140
Just screw it all up. It's crazy. This isn't right.

221
00:23:14,140 --> 00:23:16,790
I heard everything, Toto! Are you going to keep saying that gibberish?

222
00:23:16,790 --> 00:23:19,070
It's none of your business, Fortune-teller Lady.

223
00:23:19,070 --> 00:23:23,230
What? Can't you be polite to your mom?

224
00:23:23,840 --> 00:23:26,430
There's a saying that the household fails when the woman's voice is loud, so keep your voice down.

225
00:23:26,430 --> 00:23:27,850
You are the biggest problem.

226
00:23:27,850 --> 00:23:31,070
I'm sorry. I'll come at another time for the interview.

227
00:23:31,070 --> 00:23:33,510
Where are you going? Have dinner with us before you go.

228
00:23:33,510 --> 00:23:38,880
Yes. Toto might have a foul mouth, but his cooking skill is the best.

229
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:42,670
You have to try Toto's Omurice.

230
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:46,450
Bring the plate with you.

231
00:24:08,190 --> 00:24:12,270
 Dinner is always together!

232
00:24:12,270 --> 00:24:15,400
 Where are they shouting to?

233
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,540
Did you not eat for a few days?

234
00:24:59,540 --> 00:25:02,940
Why do you say it like that? It's good that she's eating well.

235
00:25:02,940 --> 00:25:07,790
That's Dad. Shitty hand skills, shitty manners, and a shitty mouth.

236
00:25:08,910 --> 00:25:12,580
I guess it was so delicious that she got stunned.

237
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:16,140
I told you that our Toto's cooking skill is the best.

238
00:25:22,780 --> 00:25:24,490
Stop giving out food!

239
00:25:24,490 --> 00:25:27,250
You feed street cats so much, so there are too many kittens now.

240
00:25:27,250 --> 00:25:28,310
What's wrong with that?

241
00:25:28,310 --> 00:25:29,820
This area becomes the cats' litter box.

242
00:25:29,820 --> 00:25:31,590
You have no heart.

243
00:25:31,590 --> 00:25:35,590
Have some compassion as much as your cooking skills.

244
00:25:35,590 --> 00:25:38,540
Why do I have to listen to this?

245
00:25:38,540 --> 00:25:41,880
- Where are you going? 
 - If we ate dinner together, today's work is over.

246
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,020
What about the dishes?

247
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:45,260
We have a part-timer now.

248
00:25:49,470 --> 00:25:51,740
Please go back to eating.

249
00:25:51,740 --> 00:25:55,320
When do we do the interview?

250
00:25:55,320 --> 00:25:56,780
We just did it.

251
00:25:56,780 --> 00:25:58,870
We just did it.

252
00:25:58,870 --> 00:26:00,130
Sorry?

253
00:26:00,130 --> 00:26:02,300
Eating dinner together was the interview.

254
00:26:02,300 --> 00:26:04,200
Didn't you know about it?

255
00:26:05,540 --> 00:26:09,260
Maybe she's confused because we are so weird.

256
00:26:12,630 --> 00:26:16,510
So what name will you be?

257
00:26:16,510 --> 00:26:17,640
Excuse me?

258
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:20,840
Your name. What did you get it?

259
00:26:23,810 --> 00:26:26,520
My name is Yu Ri.

260
00:26:26,520 --> 00:26:30,470
Yu Ri? You received a pretty name.

261
00:26:30,470 --> 00:26:33,690
Yes. My dad named me.

262
00:26:33,690 --> 00:26:35,570
Papa's discriminating.

263
00:26:35,570 --> 00:26:38,580
I think he didn't put enough time into our names.

264
00:26:38,580 --> 00:26:40,220
I know.

265
00:26:41,730 --> 00:26:44,680
Anyway, it's nice to meet you.

